The paper deals with privacy-preserving and distributed data mining, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses cryptography and distributed learning, which are sub-fields of computer security (cs.CR). The use of block coordinate descent algorithm and the focus on data partitioning suggest that the paper could also be classified under the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper's emphasis on real-world applications and evaluation of the proposed algorithm using simulated and real-world examples suggest that it could also be classified under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
